thread.title: A-W girls win team title at Patriot Invite
thread.title_full: A-W girls win team title at Patriot Invite

title: A-W girls win team title at Patriot Invite
text: Posted Oct. 19, 2015 at 9:08 PM Posted Oct. 19, 2015 at 9:08 PM Kewanee With three runners among the top 12 finishers, the Annawan-Wethersfield girls cross country team won the team title Friday at the Patriot Invite in Peoria. Kirstie Ramsey finished second among the 270 runners in 17:51, behind first-place finisher Daly Galloway of Gardner South, who ran the course in 17:22. Olivia Draminski of the Lady Titans was sixth at 18:23 and Joycelyn VanAntwerp was 12th at 18:36. Other finishers for Annawan-Wethersfield were Diana Satkauskas 41st (19:43) and Whitney Johnson 44th (19:45). That gave Annawan-Wethersfield a team a score of 104. Unity Hight School placed second with 117. Also scoring for A/W were Sarah Gomez 65th (20:21) and Rachel Cook 83rd (20:50). Kewanee High School’s Shauri Vogt placed 27th in a time of 19:06. Kewanee’s Julia King was 75th (20:40) and Katie Vickrey ran the course in 26:07 for 244th place. Bureau Valley placed 20th as a team. Runners were Haley Weidner 31st (19:18), Heather Williams 92nd (21:06), Nataleigh Nugent 116th (21:30), Hannah Williams 151st (22:17), Marissa Mungia 203rd (23:27) and Sydney Sweenie 251st (26:44). Ridgewood placed 35th with Makenna Medley 121st (21:57), Emma Steider 144th (22:35), Carlie Barman 188th (23:41), Tobi Matter 194th (23:50) and Daisy Johnson 195th (23:51). Other individual girls results were: Stark County: Brooke Rennick 52nd (19:53); and Galva-ROWVA: Lauren Hawes 67th (20:23), Kelly Harrell 129th (21:49), Annadoria Ledbetter 195th (23:11). For the boys, Kewanee High School’s Rolando Aguilar ran the course in 15:21 to finish 12th. The KHS team placed 40th. Other KHS runners were Sam Gleichman 222nd (18:51), Hunter Hand 239th (19:22), Zeke Robleto 240th (19:23), Carter Davis 284th (21:06) Isaac Hernandez 285th (21:10) and Owen VanWassenhove 286th (21:17). Galva-ROWVA placed 13th as a tean, led by Caelin Foley’s 27th-place finish in 15:55. Other finishers were Kyle Campagna 68th (16:31), Isaac Williamson 74th (16:36), Mike Bersell 99th (16:59) and Trenton Niemeyer 191st (18:31). Annawan-Wethersfield’s boys team placed 29th. Individual runners were Keith Davis 40th (16:14), Noah Dir 131st (17:26), Jacob Wolf 178th (18:08), Joe Fisher 182nd (18:14), Kyle Davis 212th (18:44), Dylan Battin 219th (18:48) and Jonathan Johnson 226th (18:57). Bureau Valley placed 31st in the team race, with Yulian Osorio at 114th (17:15), Morgan Strader 115th (17:16), Austin Catton 170th (17:57), Kurt Bitting 175th (18:04), Trevor Griffin 252nd (19:52), Robert Aukes 264th (20:18) and Jack Ritter 283rd (21:06). Ridgewood’s team placed 38th. Individuals were Andrew Hand 171st (17:58), Cameron Woodbury 173rd (17:59), Anthoney Brown 178th (18:05), Jordan Francis 193rd (18:33), Evan Sullivan 244th (19:30), Mitchell Todd 258th (20:05) and Alex Owens 271st (20:35). Stark County’s Noah Gibson ran the course in 20:32 and Dawson Dyken in 20:43. Star Courier - Kewanee, IL
